I was performing some tests, and I noticed that when you create a new issue in Confluence with the JIRA macro, an error is thrown in the log:
{code}
caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The template variable, projectId, has no value
{code}

This error just appears when you click on the "Project" field which is a required field.

Confluence is able to create the JIRA issue, however, the error message is spamming without any reason.

It would be better to suppress that message.

{panel}
*Steps to reproduce:*
# Create a _test_ page in Confluence.
# Leave the _atlassian-confluence.log_ open.
#* (i) If you're using Linux, use the {{tail -f atlassian-atlassian.log}}
# Add a JIRA macro.
# Click on the "Project" field and check the logs.
# The ERROR message is there but the Issue was created 
{panel}

